PRODUCT: RlmA(II) is a methyltransferase found in Streptococcus pneumoniae and confers resistance to mycinamicin tylosin and lincosamides. Specifically this enzyme adds a methyl group to guanosine 748 (E. coli numbering) of 23S ribosomal RNA.
PatB is an ABC transporter of Streptococcus pneumoniae that interacts with PatA to confer fluoroquinolone resistance..
